1. Kada sam bio dete, verovalo se da *magija* može da leči bolesti. (When I was a child, it was believed that *magic* could cure illnesses.)
2. Ona je bila veoma talentovana i uspešna u izvođenju *magije*. (She was very talented and successful in performing *magic*.)
3. Njena lepota imala je neku *magiju* koja je privlačila mnoge muškarce. (Her beauty had a kind of *magic* that attracted many men.)
4. Kada sam krenuo da učim o *magiji*, otkrio sam koliko je ona zapravo kompleksna. (When I started learning about *magic*, I discovered how complex it actually is.)
5. Saznao sam da postoje različite vrste *magije*, kao što su bela i crna. (I learned that there are different types of *magic*, such as white and black.)
6. Njegova knjiga je bila puna tajni i *magije*. (His book was full of secrets and *magic*.)
7. Verovali su da su im pojedini predmeti doneli sreću zahvaljujući *magiji*. (They believed that certain objects brought them luck thanks to *magic*.)
8. *Magija* koju je stvorila u svojoj glavi bila je dovoljna da se izbori sa svim svojim strahovima. (The *magic* she created in her mind was enough to overcome all her fears.)
9. Kada su videli šta je uradio, svi su pomislili da je to bila čista *magija*. (When they saw what he had done, everyone thought it was pure *magic*.)
10. Za mene, ova mala oaza u gradu ima posebnu *magiju*. (For me, this little oasis in the city has a special *magic*.)